Create a Public Azure Blob Storage Container

Allow Public Access to the Blob Service:
If you are creating the Storage Account:
When you create the storage account (xfusionst17077), in the Advanced tab, make sure you enable public access to blob data.
Select "Allow public access to blob data".

If the storage account is already created, follow these steps to allow public access:
Modify the Storage Account:
Navigate to the Storage Account xfusionst17077 in the Azure Portal.
Under the Settings section, select Configuration.
Find the Blob public access setting, and set it to Enabled.

Create the Public Blob Container:
After ensuring the storage account allows public access, go to Containers under Blob service.
Click on + Container to create the new container.
Name it xfusion-blob-802.
For Public access level, select Blob (anonymous read access for blobs only).
Click Create to finish.
